{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6d417cc3fb48d67c2e", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "63134c746e7bc9b332483706", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "question": {"text": "In normal adjustment, for a refracting telescope, the distance between objective and eye piece is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. The focal length of the objective, when the angular magnification of the telescope is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>, will be:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "3o15b", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "lgVBQ", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "Eh3oo", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "yzmDV", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;be the focal length of objective and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;is the focal length of eyepiece.</p><p>Given here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math>.</p><p>Angular magnification of telescope is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac></math>.</p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></math></p><p>Then, we have&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math></p><p>Or,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "questionLabels": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ76095181", "source": "EM", "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61